WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:12.029 --> 00:01:15.039
(All characters. locations. organizations. religions.)

3
00:01:15.039 --> 00:01:17.610
(and incidents in this drama are fictional.)

4
00:01:19.439 --> 00:01:22.310
(Episode 8)

5
00:01:47.481 --> 00:01:48.710
I knew you would come.

6
00:01:50.180 --> 00:01:51.680
It was inevitable.

7
00:02:00.231 --> 00:02:01.661
Did you think I wouldn't be able to...

8
00:02:02.390 --> 00:02:04.160
find you if you hide?

9
00:02:07.401 --> 00:02:10.470
I can't stop myself. I can't.

10
00:02:11.601 --> 00:02:12.940
I cannot.

11
00:02:13.970 --> 00:02:17.140
I told you I could see right through you.

12
00:02:18.541 --> 00:02:19.951
That you're a good guy.

13
00:02:20.981 --> 00:02:22.181
I know that.

14
00:02:23.151 --> 00:02:24.951
This feeling of inability to stop myself...

15
00:02:25.580 --> 00:02:27.420
What should I call it?

16
00:02:28.091 --> 00:02:30.720
You can't run away before you grant me my wish.

17
00:02:32.291 --> 00:02:33.660
I said you could go...

18
00:02:34.030 --> 00:02:35.690
after you grant me my wish.

19
00:02:36.030 --> 00:02:37.231
Don't you remember?

20
00:02:38.360 --> 00:02:39.871
I do not know the answer to that.

21
00:02:40.530 --> 00:02:41.601
So I can just...

22
00:02:42.371 --> 00:02:44.701
- Tak Dong Kyung. - I'm going to kill...

23
00:02:49.241 --> 00:02:52.981
So the only thing I could do is call it you.

24
00:03:33.991 --> 00:03:35.690
You've gone mad.

25
00:03:36.290 --> 00:03:39.061
- Why did you cut the bracelet? - Have you gone mad?

26
00:03:39.160 --> 00:03:40.891
Why didn't you come to me sooner?

27
00:03:40.891 --> 00:03:43.160
And how could you put a pillow under my head and leave?

28
00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:44.431
That's infuriating.

29
00:03:46.730 --> 00:03:48.000
What infuriated you?

30
00:03:48.871 --> 00:03:50.470
Not showing up or putting a pillow under your head?

31
00:03:50.470 --> 00:03:51.871
Putting a pillow under my head.

32
00:03:52.470 --> 00:03:53.470
Gosh.

33
00:04:00.980 --> 00:04:01.980
Did you just smile?

34
00:04:02.611 --> 00:04:04.651
How can you smile right now?

35
00:04:05.450 --> 00:04:06.750
You're smiling too.

36
00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:09.820
You're smiling too.

37
00:04:12.160 --> 00:04:13.891
Gosh. What an attention-seeker.

38
00:04:14.391 --> 00:04:16.030
If you were going to stay away. you should've done it right.

39
00:04:16.030 --> 00:04:17.260
Why leave me a hint?

40
00:04:20.801 --> 00:04:22.171
I was trying not to do it.

41
00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:25.801
For how long?

42
00:04:28.311 --> 00:04:29.540
As long as I could.

43
00:04:31.111 --> 00:04:33.280
You must've forgotten.

44
00:04:33.711 --> 00:04:36.581
I don't have that much time on my hands.

45
00:04:45.591 --> 00:04:46.690
I'll tell you.

46
00:04:50.730 --> 00:04:53.271
I will tell you everything.

47
00:05:24.731 --> 00:05:25.830
It's all my fault.

48
00:05:29.231 --> 00:05:30.871
You losing your parents.

49
00:05:32.340 --> 00:05:34.871
All the time you had to spend at the beach.

50
00:05:35.471 --> 00:05:36.681
All the misfortunes.

51
00:05:38.580 --> 00:05:40.611
And your illness. Everything.

52
00:05:51.221 --> 00:05:54.960
You know what? You need to learn how to communicate first.

53
00:05:55.561 --> 00:05:58.200
Why does everything you tell me sound like a riddle?

54
00:05:58.200 --> 00:06:00.070
Or give me better hints at least.

55
00:06:00.070 --> 00:06:01.531
Make it more understandable for me.

56
00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:06.340
I'm saying you're miserable...

57
00:06:08.140 --> 00:06:09.640
because I exist.

58
00:06:09.671 --> 00:06:13.481
So are you saying you're winter. darkness. and the end of everything?

59
00:06:14.650 --> 00:06:15.681
Yes.

60
00:06:16.820 --> 00:06:19.991
Hey. I like winter.

61
00:06:20.491 --> 00:06:23.320
I like the darkness of the night. and I like it when things end.

62
00:06:24.390 --> 00:06:25.861
If you think about it.

63
00:06:25.861 --> 00:06:28.731
spring. morning. and new beginnings also come because of you.

64
00:06:29.330 --> 00:06:32.061
It means you're responsible for both my misery and happiness.

65
00:06:34.801 --> 00:06:35.801
I guess...

66
00:06:36.400 --> 00:06:38.400
it's kind of like you're teasing me.

67
00:06:38.801 --> 00:06:40.371
I get mad when you bring me misery.

68
00:06:40.371 --> 00:06:41.940
but I become grateful when you bring me happiness.

69
00:06:43.481 --> 00:06:46.010
I don't like it when it rains.

70
00:06:46.440 --> 00:06:48.080
but rain is needed sometimes.

71
00:06:54.150 --> 00:06:57.320
That's what you are. You should say that.

72
00:06:58.090 --> 00:06:59.090
To whom?

73
00:06:59.090 --> 00:07:02.460
To the person who kicked you out of my life into my life.

74
00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:06.871
It's not your fault.

75
00:07:07.700 --> 00:07:10.101
Tell that person I said that.

76
00:07:16.010 --> 00:07:19.041
I got the answer right. didn't I?

77
00:07:19.241 --> 00:07:22.150
I solved your crossword puzzle.

78
00:07:29.991 --> 00:07:32.721
Hey. Don't even think about it.

79
00:07:32.991 --> 00:07:36.700
I know it's what guys do when they flirt.

80
00:07:40.070 --> 00:07:41.830
Hey. I...

81
00:08:29.250 --> 00:08:30.380
Who are you?

82
00:08:31.221 --> 00:08:32.520
Where's Dong Kyung?

83
00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:34.051
What? Whom?

84
00:08:36.890 --> 00:08:38.061
What the...

85
00:08:43.460 --> 00:08:45.760
What... Who are you?

86
00:08:46.231 --> 00:08:49.130
Excuse me? Hello?

87
00:08:56.010 --> 00:08:57.281
Where am I?

88
00:09:07.750 --> 00:09:08.890
We meet again.

89
00:09:13.830 --> 00:09:14.890
Come here.

90
00:09:15.231 --> 00:09:17.900
I'm on my way. Okay.

91
00:09:18.330 --> 00:09:20.531
No. I don't want a hot dog. I want a fish cake bar.

92
00:09:20.931 --> 00:09:23.270
Hey. they're completely different.

93
00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:26.541
Okay. Get it for me. I'll be right over.

94
00:09:27.770 --> 00:09:28.940
Where's your sister?

95
00:09:28.940 --> 00:09:31.181
My gosh. you startled me. Who are you?

96
00:09:31.210 --> 00:09:32.881
Where's Dong Kyung?

97
00:09:33.181 --> 00:09:35.980
What? Who's Dong Kyung?

98
00:09:38.480 --> 00:09:41.220
Tak Dong Kyung. She's your older sister.

99
00:09:41.990 --> 00:09:43.051
"Older sister"?

100
00:09:43.590 --> 00:09:45.061
I don't have an older sister.

101
00:09:45.561 --> 00:09:47.230
I'm an only child.

102
00:09:49.061 --> 00:09:50.200
What's his problem?

103
00:09:51.431 --> 00:09:53.931
Hey. I have no idea.

104
00:09:53.931 --> 00:09:56.070
This guy suddenly stopped me and asked me where my sister is.

105
00:09:57.740 --> 00:09:58.870
He's so freaky.

106
00:10:04.041 --> 00:10:05.541
What? Whom?

107
00:10:06.740 --> 00:10:09.551
Tak Dong Kyung. Is she not here?

108
00:10:09.710 --> 00:10:11.080
"Tak Dong Kyung"?

109
00:10:11.881 --> 00:10:14.190
Is there a writer named Tak Dong Kyung?

110
00:10:21.690 --> 00:10:22.830
Who are you?

111
00:10:25.631 --> 00:10:26.661
She sits there.

112
00:10:27.200 --> 00:10:29.230
I'm looking for Tak Dong Kyung That's her seat.

113
00:10:30.901 --> 00:10:32.740
I think you've come to the wrong place.

114
00:10:34.740 --> 00:10:35.811
Hey.

115
00:10:44.521 --> 00:10:45.781
Who's Tak Dong Kyung?

116
00:10:51.791 --> 00:10:53.960
That's my seat.

117
00:11:21.720 --> 00:11:22.720
No one...

118
00:11:23.791 --> 00:11:25.860
No one knows Dong Kyung.

119
00:11:27.661 --> 00:11:31.330
She no longer exists in this world.

120
00:11:33.631 --> 00:11:35.470
Where is this place?

121
00:11:36.200 --> 00:11:38.301
I swear I was at the hospital.

122
00:11:39.440 --> 00:11:40.610
Is this a dream?

123
00:11:41.340 --> 00:11:42.710
It's not a dream.

124
00:11:44.110 --> 00:11:46.210
I just stole you for a moment.

125
00:11:46.950 --> 00:11:48.011
From this guy.

126
00:11:49.610 --> 00:11:51.850
You wanted to know what I planted in this pot.

127
00:11:52.651 --> 00:11:53.950
What is it?

128
00:11:59.090 --> 00:12:00.220
Possibility.

129
00:12:00.490 --> 00:12:02.661
It fed off of your misery.

130
00:12:05.460 --> 00:12:08.700
I wanted to show it to you. You helped it grow.

131
00:12:10.171 --> 00:12:11.240
I helped it grow?

132
00:12:11.240 --> 00:12:14.240
It's the first time he pitied someone more than himself.

133
00:12:39.161 --> 00:12:43.230
(Be careful not to fall)

134
00:12:51.240 --> 00:12:55.080
"How did you become an adult so quickly?"

135
00:12:55.450 --> 00:12:57.181
"That's a secret."

136
00:12:57.651 --> 00:12:58.820
"Please tell me."

137
00:12:59.350 --> 00:13:01.051
"I also want to become an adult."

138
00:13:01.620 --> 00:13:03.350
"I'm still just a kid."

139
00:13:03.860 --> 00:13:06.820
"But you can't become an adult."

140
00:13:07.830 --> 00:13:08.931
"Why not?"

141
00:13:09.360 --> 00:13:11.931
"Because you're not qualified."

142
00:13:12.700 --> 00:13:13.771
"No."

143
00:13:14.171 --> 00:13:17.001
"I'm sick of living as a puppet."

144
00:13:17.641 --> 00:13:19.771
"I want to grow up and become an adult."

145
00:13:20.970 --> 00:13:22.840
"You can become an adult."

146
00:13:23.411 --> 00:13:26.840
"But in order to do so. you need to become qualified."

147
00:13:27.651 --> 00:13:29.181
"What do I need to do?"

148
00:13:29.811 --> 00:13:31.151
"It's simple."

149
00:13:31.580 --> 00:13:34.521
"You just always need to try your best to be nice."

150
00:13:39.090 --> 00:13:40.220
I guess it's you.

151
00:13:42.661 --> 00:13:44.431
You made him become like that.

152
00:13:45.801 --> 00:13:47.200
You kicked him out.

153
00:13:47.700 --> 00:13:50.600
You told him he's responsible for all my misery.

154
00:13:51.200 --> 00:13:53.840
- Yes. it was me. - Why did you do that?

155
00:13:55.110 --> 00:13:56.340
For you.

156
00:13:56.740 --> 00:13:57.940
What's that supposed to mean?

157
00:13:57.940 --> 00:14:00.751
You will become heartbroken no matter what you choose to do.

158
00:14:01.181 --> 00:14:02.651
Whether you make the world come to an end...

159
00:14:02.651 --> 00:14:05.181
or kill someone you love in order to live.

160
00:14:07.291 --> 00:14:09.320
But you see. I love him too.

161
00:14:09.850 --> 00:14:11.521
That's why I did this.

162
00:14:14.661 --> 00:14:17.460
What are you?

163
00:14:17.901 --> 00:14:18.960
Me?

164
00:14:20.431 --> 00:14:22.531
I'm the order of this world that's been around for many years.

165
00:14:23.070 --> 00:14:24.840
A loner that's been around for a very long time.

166
00:14:25.271 --> 00:14:27.240
I'm a long friend of yours.

167
00:14:28.041 --> 00:14:30.881
I've watched over this world longer than he has.

168
00:14:31.210 --> 00:14:34.051
And I always longed for you to be happy.

169
00:14:34.051 --> 00:14:36.980
Then why can't you just let us be happy?

170
00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:38.681
Then what kind of meaning would it have?

171
00:14:38.980 --> 00:14:42.921
What if you could easily have everything you want forever?

172
00:14:43.990 --> 00:14:47.391
You'll find out that kind of life is meaningless.

173
00:14:49.031 --> 00:14:50.960
So what do you want from me?

174
00:15:01.970 --> 00:15:03.470
What's that doing here?

175
00:15:03.470 --> 00:15:04.940
What do I want?

176
00:15:07.181 --> 00:15:08.251
What about you? What do you want?

177
00:15:17.720 --> 00:15:21.860
The fate of everything that's inside depends on your love.

178
00:15:23.261 --> 00:15:24.531
Isn't that scary?

179
00:15:25.431 --> 00:15:27.801
You should no longer be miserable because of him.

180
00:15:28.171 --> 00:15:29.470
That's what I wanted to tell you.

181
00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:39.210
No.

182
00:15:39.541 --> 00:15:41.811
He doesn't make me miserable.

183
00:15:41.811 --> 00:15:44.080
Don't say that to me or him.

184
00:15:44.350 --> 00:15:47.620
I was never miserable because of him.

185
00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:54.960
I always liked your answer.

186
00:15:55.490 --> 00:15:57.460
Although I must say. it's quite straightforward.

187
00:15:59.261 --> 00:16:02.370
I'm guessing this was enough to blackmail him.

188
00:16:04.240 --> 00:16:06.570
Go. He's at the end of the road.

189
00:16:11.840 --> 00:16:13.511
Knock lightly before you open the door.

190
00:16:13.511 --> 00:16:14.580
You know that. right?

191
00:17:10.271 --> 00:17:11.301
You really...

192
00:17:12.870 --> 00:17:15.641
You really are here.

193
00:17:20.511 --> 00:17:21.511
Hi.

194
00:17:22.181 --> 00:17:23.281
What's your deal?

195
00:17:24.580 --> 00:17:26.251
- Why are you... - I don't know either.

196
00:17:26.251 --> 00:17:28.291
I opened my eyes. and I was here.

197
00:17:28.891 --> 00:17:31.261
She said to keep walking this way...

198
00:17:57.538 --> 00:17:58.637
The deity's garden.

199
00:18:00.207 --> 00:18:02.877
That's where you were. The deity's garden.

200
00:18:07.978 --> 00:18:10.917
Wow. She's really a deity?

201
00:18:13.687 --> 00:18:14.718
That's good.

202
00:18:15.687 --> 00:18:17.258
I denied it.

203
00:18:17.427 --> 00:18:19.988
I said my being miserable was absolutely not your fault.

204
00:18:20.427 --> 00:18:21.498
Hold on.

205
00:18:21.498 --> 00:18:23.998
Did I or did I not say "absolutely"?

206
00:18:24.127 --> 00:18:26.427
I feel like I did. at least in my mind.

207
00:18:28.097 --> 00:18:30.038
- What did she say? - She laughed.

208
00:18:30.397 --> 00:18:32.367
Why did she laugh? That little runt.

209
00:18:33.308 --> 00:18:35.407
Probably because it was funny. Even I find it funny.

210
00:18:36.338 --> 00:18:38.877
- You're fearless. - I wish.

211
00:18:38.877 --> 00:18:40.607
I was terrified.

212
00:18:40.607 --> 00:18:42.278
I wondered if I was in paradise...

213
00:18:42.278 --> 00:18:43.478
or in the land of torment.

214
00:18:44.248 --> 00:18:45.917
Still. I had to say what I thought.

215
00:18:45.917 --> 00:18:47.088
Me too.

216
00:18:49.488 --> 00:18:50.558
I was scared...

217
00:18:51.528 --> 00:18:53.157
because no one remembered you.

218
00:19:06.637 --> 00:19:07.637
Dong Kyung!

219
00:19:08.877 --> 00:19:09.978
I knew it.

220
00:19:09.978 --> 00:19:11.778
You broke out of the hospital to come home?

221
00:19:14.478 --> 00:19:16.147
What's wrong with this place?

222
00:19:22.818 --> 00:19:24.457
What is all of this?

223
00:19:24.957 --> 00:19:26.088
What is this?

224
00:19:26.887 --> 00:19:28.427
What... What is this?

225
00:19:30.897 --> 00:19:31.998
Darn it.

226
00:19:39.667 --> 00:19:40.838
What is this?

227
00:19:55.988 --> 00:20:00.927
So... You are... You're a deity?

228
00:20:01.758 --> 00:20:03.028
Is that it?

229
00:20:03.657 --> 00:20:05.798
Not a deity. Doom.

230
00:20:05.798 --> 00:20:08.097
That's the same thing.

231
00:20:08.397 --> 00:20:11.538
It's actually not the same thing. Speaking from experience.

232
00:20:12.068 --> 00:20:14.338
That's probably easier for him to understand.

233
00:20:14.578 --> 00:20:15.607
Is it?

234
00:20:15.607 --> 00:20:17.748
What do you people take me for?

235
00:20:18.447 --> 00:20:19.907
Give it a rest!

236
00:20:19.907 --> 00:20:21.518
I'm not stupid.

237
00:20:24.078 --> 00:20:25.347
You're teasing me. aren't you?

238
00:20:26.218 --> 00:20:27.687
Who are you people?

239
00:20:29.288 --> 00:20:31.288
Keep your head on straight.

240
00:20:31.288 --> 00:20:32.528
Don't fall for this.

241
00:20:32.758 --> 00:20:34.857
"Keep your head on straight."

242
00:20:34.998 --> 00:20:36.427
"Don't fall for this."

243
00:20:37.097 --> 00:20:39.127
Did I say that out loud?

244
00:20:40.127 --> 00:20:42.697
No. It was just a coincidence. Yes. a coincidence.

245
00:20:42.798 --> 00:20:46.068
"No. It was just a coincidence. Yes. a coincidence."

246
00:20:48.437 --> 00:20:50.677
You both like coincidences so much. Is it in your blood?

247
00:20:51.177 --> 00:20:52.607
Can you see into my heart?

248
00:20:53.508 --> 00:20:54.978
Don't look.

249
00:20:54.978 --> 00:20:56.518
To be more precise.

250
00:20:56.518 --> 00:20:58.187
it's more like he hears it.

251
00:20:58.187 --> 00:21:00.588
- That's right. - Don't listen.

252
00:21:00.917 --> 00:21:02.218
Did you plan this with him?

253
00:21:04.088 --> 00:21:05.228
Have I lost my mind?

254
00:21:05.228 --> 00:21:07.228
Did I lose it because I was overwhelmed?

255
00:21:08.728 --> 00:21:09.957
Look at me.

256
00:21:10.328 --> 00:21:11.768
Do I look sane to you?

257
00:21:12.798 --> 00:21:14.538
How many fingers do you see?

258
00:21:14.838 --> 00:21:16.568
- 2. - You see 2?

259
00:21:17.298 --> 00:21:18.407
It's three.

260
00:21:20.238 --> 00:21:22.677
- It's 3? - It's 2. idiot.

261
00:21:23.707 --> 00:21:25.578
Do you still see your sister?

262
00:21:29.478 --> 00:21:30.677
Don't make him cry.

263
00:21:31.248 --> 00:21:32.488
You're worse than I am.

264
00:21:32.647 --> 00:21:35.457
Do something. He can't handle it.

265
00:21:35.457 --> 00:21:37.627
Do what? He'll have to accept it as you did.

266
00:21:37.627 --> 00:21:38.887
You know. what you always do.

267
00:21:38.887 --> 00:21:41.058
What do I always do? I don't know what you mean.

268
00:21:41.627 --> 00:21:43.397
Are you really a deity?

269
00:21:44.528 --> 00:21:47.697
Are you doom or something like that?

270
00:21:50.367 --> 00:21:53.008
That means... Are you here...

271
00:21:53.968 --> 00:21:56.707
to take my sister away?

272
00:21:56.707 --> 00:21:59.308
Why are you saying that?

273
00:21:59.308 --> 00:22:00.308
No.

274
00:22:02.048 --> 00:22:03.347
I'm here to save her.

275
00:22:09.187 --> 00:22:11.627
Do you mean it? Will you really save her?

276
00:22:12.588 --> 00:22:15.758
Yes. My prayers worked.

277
00:22:16.228 --> 00:22:17.498
That's not why.

278
00:22:18.228 --> 00:22:20.197
Your prayers don't come to me. They go elsewhere.

279
00:22:21.068 --> 00:22:23.897
Are there departments and stuff like that?

280
00:22:24.338 --> 00:22:26.137
Yes. so...

281
00:22:27.808 --> 00:22:29.407
forget everything and sleep.

282
00:22:30.207 --> 00:22:31.248
What?

283
00:22:32.278 --> 00:22:34.847
Forget everything and sleep.

284
00:22:39.947 --> 00:22:41.088
I did something.

285
00:23:02.907 --> 00:23:03.907
Are you up?

286
00:23:06.478 --> 00:23:07.508
Dong Kyung!

287
00:23:08.377 --> 00:23:09.417
Dong Kyung!

288
00:23:12.617 --> 00:23:13.818
Are you okay?

289
00:23:14.117 --> 00:23:16.818
I was so scared when I got the call.

290
00:23:16.818 --> 00:23:19.828
I thought I'd never see you again.

291
00:23:20.028 --> 00:23:22.258
So why did you worry the kid?

292
00:23:24.828 --> 00:23:26.127
You were here?

293
00:23:26.927 --> 00:23:29.798
What took you so long to come?

294
00:23:29.798 --> 00:23:31.367
I was so scared all alone...

295
00:23:33.068 --> 00:23:34.407
I was scared.

296
00:23:38.147 --> 00:23:40.677
Why do I feel like I was with him until just now?

297
00:23:41.518 --> 00:23:43.518
- You must've had a dream. - A dream?

298
00:23:43.978 --> 00:23:47.347
My brother-in-law must like me a lot.

299
00:23:47.758 --> 00:23:49.457
Yes. I do.

300
00:23:49.788 --> 00:23:51.488
If you're done professing your love. let's go.

301
00:23:52.258 --> 00:23:54.187
Go? Go where?

302
00:23:54.597 --> 00:23:56.357
- Home. - Yes. home.

303
00:23:57.968 --> 00:23:59.127
Why would we go home?

304
00:24:00.468 --> 00:24:02.068
Wait. Why are you changed?

305
00:24:02.068 --> 00:24:03.468
I'm fine now.

306
00:24:03.468 --> 00:24:04.707
You are not fine.

307
00:24:04.707 --> 00:24:06.867
The doctor said he needed to run more tests.

308
00:24:07.137 --> 00:24:09.907
- Sun Kyung. - Stop her.

309
00:24:11.578 --> 00:24:14.207
What? Are you two in on it together?

310
00:24:17.117 --> 00:24:19.748
No! I won't go! Definitely not!

311
00:24:19.748 --> 00:24:21.157
I won't budge!

312
00:24:21.558 --> 00:24:22.617
Sun Kyung?

313
00:24:22.617 --> 00:24:24.357
Why are you doing this too?

314
00:24:24.357 --> 00:24:26.157
- If you keep doing this. I... - I'm a doctor.

315
00:24:31.998 --> 00:24:33.068
A doctor?

316
00:24:35.498 --> 00:24:36.667
Dong Kyung.

317
00:24:37.268 --> 00:24:38.407
Ji Na!

318
00:24:38.867 --> 00:24:40.008
Ji Na. the thing is...

319
00:24:40.008 --> 00:24:42.707
I couldn't tell you back then. but I planned to tell you...

320
00:24:42.707 --> 00:24:44.407
Seriously. you...

321
00:24:44.407 --> 00:24:46.707
Seriously. I wanted to tell you several times.

322
00:24:50.417 --> 00:24:51.647
What do you want to eat?

323
00:24:53.048 --> 00:24:54.288
What do you want to do?

324
00:24:54.288 --> 00:24:56.187
What do you want to have? Where do you want to go?

325
00:24:57.417 --> 00:24:59.288
I'll do it all for you from now on.

326
00:25:00.427 --> 00:25:01.697
So tell me.

327
00:25:02.058 --> 00:25:03.897
Say the word. What should I do for you?

328
00:25:10.068 --> 00:25:12.667
Hey. how could you do this to me?

329
00:25:13.308 --> 00:25:15.677
How could you ask me that?

330
00:25:16.238 --> 00:25:18.078
You said you'd do everything I asked.

331
00:25:18.078 --> 00:25:19.808
I really want to go home.

332
00:25:19.808 --> 00:25:21.518
I'm really fine.

333
00:25:21.518 --> 00:25:23.748
- Hey. turn left here. - I know.

334
00:25:23.748 --> 00:25:25.117
I'm not fine.

335
00:25:25.488 --> 00:25:26.518
Turn the car around.

336
00:25:26.548 --> 00:25:28.218
Do it now!

337
00:25:28.288 --> 00:25:30.887
Gosh. She's so loud that I can't focus on driving.

338
00:25:31.088 --> 00:25:32.288
At this rate. the four of us will die.

339
00:25:32.288 --> 00:25:34.657
- Don't talk about dying! - Don't talk about dying!

340
00:25:36.697 --> 00:25:39.667
I guess you have a type for the people you keep around.

341
00:25:41.798 --> 00:25:43.038
Hold on.

342
00:25:43.937 --> 00:25:45.707
He's been getting on my nerves.

343
00:25:46.107 --> 00:25:48.338
Who is that guy? Why does he keep dropping his honorifics to me?

344
00:25:48.338 --> 00:25:50.377
- I never talked to you. - Hey.

345
00:25:50.437 --> 00:25:53.347
I'm sorry. Picking up a fight with people is his habit.

346
00:25:53.347 --> 00:25:54.518
Hey.

347
00:25:54.778 --> 00:25:56.518
Who are you? Answer me.

348
00:25:56.518 --> 00:26:00.588
Listen. You shouldn't approach this so emotionally.

349
00:26:00.588 --> 00:26:02.488
I know everything because I've tried it all.

350
00:26:02.488 --> 00:26:04.558
- You should... - Shut it.

351
00:26:07.728 --> 00:26:10.528
Stop it! Gosh.

352
00:26:20.107 --> 00:26:22.238
What did your doctor exactly say?

353
00:26:23.907 --> 00:26:25.707
I have glioblastomas.

354
00:26:25.707 --> 00:26:28.917
And I have about three months left. No.

355
00:26:29.018 --> 00:26:31.588
I probably have two months left by now.

356
00:26:33.018 --> 00:26:34.857
Get up right now. Let's go to the hospital now.

357
00:26:34.857 --> 00:26:36.417
Let's go and get that surgery.

358
00:26:36.417 --> 00:26:38.788
Ji Na. Actually.

359
00:26:38.988 --> 00:26:40.588
that guy over there is a doctor.

360
00:26:40.588 --> 00:26:42.627
I don't care if he's a doctor or not.

361
00:26:42.627 --> 00:26:45.127
You're her brother. You should try to stop her. What are you doing?

362
00:26:45.127 --> 00:26:47.468
The surgery can't guarantee that I'll live.

363
00:26:47.828 --> 00:26:50.197
I could die from the surgery too. On the table.

364
00:26:50.197 --> 00:26:51.238
- Hey. - Dong Kyung.

365
00:26:51.867 --> 00:26:52.968
I'll save her.

366
00:26:54.978 --> 00:26:56.377
I'll save her life.

367
00:27:01.078 --> 00:27:03.877
Why do you look so surprised? I already told you that.

368
00:27:10.117 --> 00:27:11.457
Who is he?

369
00:27:11.828 --> 00:27:13.657
Why does he keep trying to sound cool without the honorifics?

370
00:27:13.657 --> 00:27:14.798
I can hear you.

371
00:27:15.528 --> 00:27:17.558
He's Dong Kyung's boyfriend. He's a doctor.

372
00:27:17.627 --> 00:27:18.897
That's even louder.

373
00:27:19.228 --> 00:27:20.367
A doctor?

374
00:27:20.367 --> 00:27:22.298
Are you sure? Did you check him out?

375
00:27:22.798 --> 00:27:25.667
Well. I didn't check him out.

376
00:27:25.937 --> 00:27:27.367
But he is her boyfriend for sure.

377
00:27:27.407 --> 00:27:29.907
And they are head over heels for each other.

378
00:27:30.008 --> 00:27:32.107
What? No way.

379
00:27:32.107 --> 00:27:34.947
If she fell in love. she would have told me right away...

380
00:27:36.718 --> 00:27:37.847
He's the guy.

381
00:27:38.318 --> 00:27:41.488
The guy from the hospital... The funeral!

382
00:27:41.488 --> 00:27:43.488
The guy you said you wanted to fall in love with.

383
00:27:44.857 --> 00:27:46.828
You talked about me a lot.

384
00:27:47.627 --> 00:27:50.528
What? What happened at the funeral?

385
00:27:51.157 --> 00:27:52.268
How come I don't know about it?

386
00:27:52.367 --> 00:27:54.068
Is there anything you actually know?

387
00:27:55.597 --> 00:27:57.897
Right. You don't know anything.

388
00:27:58.038 --> 00:27:59.367
You didn't even know that you should've called me...

389
00:27:59.367 --> 00:28:01.107
when you found out about her condition.

390
00:28:01.107 --> 00:28:03.937
No. that's not it. Dong Kyung told me not to tell anyone.

391
00:28:03.937 --> 00:28:06.407
Since when did you do what your sister told you?

392
00:28:06.707 --> 00:28:07.978
But I still told you...

393
00:28:07.978 --> 00:28:09.917
even when she told me not to tell you.

394
00:28:09.917 --> 00:28:11.218
You couldn't even look me in the eye before.

395
00:28:11.218 --> 00:28:12.718
but you're raising your voice at me now.

396
00:28:12.718 --> 00:28:14.988
- So you're a man now. Is that it? - Stop it.

397
00:28:16.288 --> 00:28:17.657
You two should go now.

398
00:28:19.058 --> 00:28:20.127
You want us to go?

399
00:28:20.957 --> 00:28:23.728
Who did you mean by "you two"? Were you talking to these two?

400
00:28:23.957 --> 00:28:25.167
You two.

401
00:28:26.028 --> 00:28:27.197
I can't leave.

402
00:28:27.197 --> 00:28:28.998
I can't leave you all alone.

403
00:28:29.068 --> 00:28:30.367
I won't be alone.

404
00:28:31.738 --> 00:28:33.367
I live with him.

405
00:28:36.707 --> 00:28:39.407
I'm going to sleep with him again today.

406
00:28:41.207 --> 00:28:42.248
What?

407
00:28:50.657 --> 00:28:52.957
I never knew she was so bold.

408
00:28:54.728 --> 00:28:56.498
She changed after getting diagnosed with her condition.

409
00:28:57.258 --> 00:28:59.528
But she has the right to do that.

410
00:29:00.427 --> 00:29:02.667
He knew about her condition from the get-go.

411
00:29:02.667 --> 00:29:04.097
but he's still seeing her.

412
00:29:06.367 --> 00:29:09.107
- Tak Sun Kyung. - Yes?

413
00:29:09.177 --> 00:29:10.437
You changed a bit.

414
00:29:10.637 --> 00:29:12.177
What? Me?

415
00:29:12.177 --> 00:29:14.917
Gosh. no. I never change.

416
00:29:14.917 --> 00:29:16.748
I didn't get to finish what I told you earlier.

417
00:29:22.157 --> 00:29:23.588
You're way more mature now.

418
00:29:24.657 --> 00:29:25.927
Nicely done.

419
00:29:27.427 --> 00:29:29.657
- What? - I'm patting you on the back...

420
00:29:29.657 --> 00:29:31.798
for going through this alone. You must've been in pain.

421
00:29:33.568 --> 00:29:35.397
From now on. let's suffer together.

422
00:29:35.667 --> 00:29:38.338
Let's try hard in where we are and give it our all.

423
00:29:38.338 --> 00:29:39.407
Okay?

424
00:29:41.167 --> 00:29:43.338
Don't get scared just because you think you're alone.

425
00:29:43.778 --> 00:29:46.447
You're Dong Kyung's brother. So you're a brother to me too.

426
00:29:49.447 --> 00:29:51.078
So keep an eye on her and call me right away...

427
00:29:51.078 --> 00:29:53.018
if something happens. Okay?

428
00:29:53.018 --> 00:29:55.558
If you don't call me. I'll crush your fingers.

429
00:29:56.558 --> 00:29:57.588
No.

430
00:29:58.058 --> 00:30:00.357
You really got it wrong. It's not fair.

431
00:30:00.657 --> 00:30:01.798
What?

432
00:30:03.457 --> 00:30:06.528
Ma'am. It's not fair. ma'am. Gosh.

433
00:30:06.528 --> 00:30:07.867
You little...

434
00:30:07.927 --> 00:30:09.498
- She's the little one. - Hey!

435
00:30:09.867 --> 00:30:11.968
- Goodness. You startled me. - Do you have a death wish?

436
00:30:11.968 --> 00:30:13.367
As if!

437
00:30:13.468 --> 00:30:15.778
Hey. I told you to stop getting cheeky with me.

438
00:30:15.778 --> 00:30:17.078
What are you talking about?

439
00:30:17.078 --> 00:30:18.177
I'm letting you have your way.

440
00:30:18.177 --> 00:30:19.677
You're unbelievable.

441
00:30:33.988 --> 00:30:35.197
What a hectic day.

442
00:30:35.197 --> 00:30:36.728
I still have to clean up even on a hectic day.

443
00:30:36.728 --> 00:30:38.228
This is so not fair.

444
00:30:38.228 --> 00:30:39.768
So why did you cause trouble?

445
00:30:40.367 --> 00:30:41.697
You're saying this is my fault?

446
00:30:41.697 --> 00:30:44.367
It's your fault. It's because you disappeared on me.

447
00:30:45.038 --> 00:30:47.667
I didn't know that you'd take such an extreme approach.

448
00:30:47.667 --> 00:30:50.707
You'd better watch out. If you don't listen to me...

449
00:30:50.707 --> 00:30:53.078
I didn't know you'd use yourself as leverage.

450
00:30:56.117 --> 00:30:58.187
And I didn't know it would work on me.

451
00:31:03.387 --> 00:31:05.387
How come you don't know so many things?

452
00:31:06.588 --> 00:31:10.298
- You're right. - There's so much I must teach you.

453
00:31:14.268 --> 00:31:15.867
- What? - Your hand.

454
00:31:40.988 --> 00:31:42.427
Let's live together.

455
00:31:45.167 --> 00:31:46.927
Let's continue to live together.

456
00:31:50.897 --> 00:31:52.107
We can...

457
00:31:53.707 --> 00:31:55.078
sleep together again today.

458
00:32:45.788 --> 00:32:49.758
The fate of everything that's inside depends on your love.

459
00:32:51.328 --> 00:32:52.468
Isn't that scary?

460
00:33:10.318 --> 00:33:11.548
Good evening.

461
00:33:12.687 --> 00:33:13.788
Are you having fun?

462
00:33:15.457 --> 00:33:16.718
I'm not bored.

463
00:33:17.157 --> 00:33:18.687
Leave her alone.

464
00:33:18.687 --> 00:33:20.687
I left her alone.

465
00:33:20.857 --> 00:33:22.597
I just got in your way.

466
00:33:23.197 --> 00:33:24.828
What is it that you want?

467
00:33:24.828 --> 00:33:26.068
I was wrong.

468
00:33:27.728 --> 00:33:29.667
She loves you.

469
00:33:31.298 --> 00:33:32.937
She scolded me.

470
00:33:33.508 --> 00:33:35.607
She said she was never miserable because of you.

471
00:33:37.907 --> 00:33:40.107
I always wish that I'm wrong.

472
00:33:40.808 --> 00:33:43.018
I hope you guys are right.

473
00:33:46.248 --> 00:33:48.187
But we're always wrong.

474
00:33:49.117 --> 00:33:50.488
And you're always right.

475
00:34:11.008 --> 00:34:12.848
False hope is hope too.

476
00:34:13.178 --> 00:34:14.977
False love is still love.

477
00:34:29.126 --> 00:34:31.485
Have you tried calling Ms. Tak?

478
00:34:32.295 --> 00:34:33.655
She won't even answer Mr. Park's calls.

479
00:34:33.655 --> 00:34:34.956
so I'm sure she won't answer mine.

480
00:34:35.365 --> 00:34:37.896
- This is crazy. - Should I try calling her?

481
00:34:39.195 --> 00:34:40.436
You sound awfully confident.

482
00:34:40.766 --> 00:34:42.836
Then how about we go visit her at the hospital?

483
00:34:42.836 --> 00:34:44.635
She won't let us in.

484
00:34:45.336 --> 00:34:49.005
She probably needs time. and so do we.

485
00:34:50.545 --> 00:34:53.976
I bet Ms. Tak's going through a hard time right now.

486
00:34:55.186 --> 00:34:56.416
I wonder what she's doing.

487
00:35:03.856 --> 00:35:05.356
- It's not there. - We need to see it now.

488
00:35:05.356 --> 00:35:06.525
Let's see it!

489
00:35:06.626 --> 00:35:08.695
(It's too high up. I want to...)

490
00:35:08.925 --> 00:35:11.066
It's too high up here

491
00:35:12.666 --> 00:35:13.936
I want to

492
00:35:14.595 --> 00:35:17.206
"It's too high up here." Yes. that's what it is.

493
00:35:17.306 --> 00:35:18.476
I didn't get to hear the second part.

494
00:35:18.476 --> 00:35:19.836
Hey. did you hear it?

495
00:35:20.976 --> 00:35:23.106
At least wipe your hand before touching the remote.

496
00:35:23.106 --> 00:35:25.445
My hand is clean. This doesn't have crumbs.

497
00:35:28.045 --> 00:35:30.816
Oh. my. my. my

498
00:35:30.816 --> 00:35:33.286
I want to share everything with you

499
00:35:35.056 --> 00:35:36.126
By the way.

500
00:35:36.925 --> 00:35:39.396
you didn't have to get me flowers.

501
00:35:40.126 --> 00:35:41.255
I didn't buy them.

502
00:35:41.795 --> 00:35:43.566
- Then? - I came across them.

503
00:35:45.965 --> 00:35:48.036
How cliche.

504
00:35:49.836 --> 00:35:51.206
"I came across them."

505
00:35:51.206 --> 00:35:52.876
Where did you learn that line?

506
00:35:53.235 --> 00:35:54.405
My gosh.

507
00:36:07.956 --> 00:36:09.755
(Dalgona)

508
00:36:10.786 --> 00:36:11.896
Hey. Ms. Dalgona.

509
00:36:14.996 --> 00:36:16.226
I heard the news.

510
00:36:18.496 --> 00:36:21.135
I heard you fought with Jijo King at the team dinner.

511
00:36:21.135 --> 00:36:22.365
I feel like it's my fault.

512
00:36:22.365 --> 00:36:25.536
What are you talking about? It's not your fault at all.

513
00:36:25.536 --> 00:36:27.005
Yes. it is.

514
00:36:27.476 --> 00:36:30.376
I heard you quit. So I quit too.

515
00:36:31.045 --> 00:36:32.045
What?

516
00:36:32.045 --> 00:36:34.746
I decided not to renew my contract with Life Story.

517
00:36:36.686 --> 00:36:39.755
But then again. I guess that won't matter...

518
00:36:39.755 --> 00:36:40.755
if I fail to recover.

519
00:36:43.025 --> 00:36:44.086
Recover from what?

520
00:36:45.456 --> 00:36:46.856
I'm getting surgery next month.

521
00:36:47.655 --> 00:36:49.365
I'm going to try chemotherapy.

522
00:36:50.126 --> 00:36:53.566
There's a story I really want to write.

523
00:36:54.365 --> 00:36:56.936
I'm going to write it and sell it. so they can turn it into a drama.

524
00:36:56.936 --> 00:36:58.166
The genre is teenage romance.

525
00:36:58.905 --> 00:37:00.976
I've already come up with the characters.

526
00:37:04.876 --> 00:37:07.775
(I love you. Park Young!)

527
00:37:08.746 --> 00:37:09.985
(I love you. Park Young!)

528
00:37:12.255 --> 00:37:14.115
Yes. it's him.

529
00:37:15.586 --> 00:37:17.726
He's the character I chose.

530
00:37:19.726 --> 00:37:21.965
Do you find it funny that a middle-aged lady likes him?

531
00:37:22.525 --> 00:37:23.795
What? No.

532
00:37:24.266 --> 00:37:25.896
I don't care if you find it funny.

533
00:37:27.036 --> 00:37:28.066
The thing is.

534
00:37:28.865 --> 00:37:30.865
he's the only person that makes me smile.

535
00:37:34.936 --> 00:37:37.945
It's not funny. I don't find it funny at all.

536
00:37:38.505 --> 00:37:41.945
What's funny about that? I think it's amazing.

537
00:37:42.845 --> 00:37:44.345
Once I finish writing this.

538
00:37:44.686 --> 00:37:46.856
you can be the first person to read it.

539
00:37:49.086 --> 00:37:50.456
Probably around next year.

540
00:37:51.825 --> 00:37:54.195
We both would've gotten our surgeries by then.

541
00:37:54.996 --> 00:37:58.465
People get tingles in their hearts when cherry blossoms bloom.

542
00:37:58.465 --> 00:37:59.865
That's when romance novels are very popular.

543
00:38:02.005 --> 00:38:04.606
- But the thing is... - Ms. Tak. you see.

544
00:38:05.536 --> 00:38:08.135
you feel the urge to live if you find yourself smiling a lot.

545
00:38:09.746 --> 00:38:11.976
So you should love someone.

546
00:38:13.215 --> 00:38:15.586
Love someone who makes you smile.

547
00:38:39.306 --> 00:38:41.336
- What's going on? - What do you mean?

548
00:38:44.275 --> 00:38:45.715
What are you doing here?

549
00:38:45.876 --> 00:38:48.686
- I came to pick you up. - You came to pick me up?

550
00:38:49.186 --> 00:38:50.516
I was worried you might run away.

551
00:38:52.516 --> 00:38:53.786
Stop being funny.

552
00:38:54.615 --> 00:38:55.985
I'm glad you found it funny.

553
00:39:04.925 --> 00:39:07.235
Don't get the wrong idea. This is just...

554
00:39:07.235 --> 00:39:08.766
I know. You're recharging.

555
00:39:09.806 --> 00:39:11.066
No.

556
00:39:11.066 --> 00:39:13.275
I'm holding your hand because I want to.

557
00:39:14.775 --> 00:39:15.945
Do you know something?

558
00:39:15.945 --> 00:39:18.746
Tons of people come here in spring.

559
00:39:19.275 --> 00:39:21.376
- Why? - To see cherry blossoms.

560
00:39:21.816 --> 00:39:25.115
Cherry blossoms bloom starting from here to all the way over there.

561
00:39:27.385 --> 00:39:29.025
If I knew I was going to die.

562
00:39:29.025 --> 00:39:31.385
I would've gone out last spring a lot more often to see flowers.

563
00:39:32.056 --> 00:39:33.956
I had no idea that was going to be my last time.

564
00:39:49.575 --> 00:39:52.215
What is this? Did you just do this?

565
00:39:52.775 --> 00:39:53.775
Yes.

566
00:39:57.016 --> 00:39:59.155
It really feels like spring.

567
00:39:59.255 --> 00:40:02.126
It really is spring. Although it won't last long.

568
00:40:03.586 --> 00:40:05.255
We just flew back in time a little.

569
00:40:05.255 --> 00:40:07.255
It's nothing much.

570
00:40:07.496 --> 00:40:09.795
Yes. you're incredible. I'll give you that.

571
00:40:14.936 --> 00:40:17.005
It's beautiful.

572
00:40:19.675 --> 00:40:22.106
I only have good memories of spring.

573
00:40:22.405 --> 00:40:24.606
A long time ago. when there were cherry blossoms just like now.

574
00:40:24.606 --> 00:40:26.075
my parents. Sun Kyung. and I...

575
00:40:26.075 --> 00:40:28.115
went to ride the Ferris wheel together.

576
00:40:28.575 --> 00:40:31.416
I'm as happy as I was that day.

577
00:40:39.155 --> 00:40:40.155
Hey.

578
00:40:43.896 --> 00:40:45.025
I like you.

579
00:40:55.306 --> 00:40:57.606
I said I like you.

580
00:41:01.516 --> 00:41:03.985
It feels nice to get that off my chest. See you.

581
00:41:05.615 --> 00:41:07.416
I'm not coming home tonight.

582
00:41:07.416 --> 00:41:08.856
I'm sleeping over at Ji Na's.

583
00:41:34.416 --> 00:41:35.516
Ji Na!

584
00:41:36.115 --> 00:41:37.945
What is that? What's that in your mouth?

585
00:41:37.945 --> 00:41:40.916
No. I... I didn't even light it up. It was just in between my lips.

586
00:41:41.286 --> 00:41:43.356
I told you not to smoke.

587
00:41:43.356 --> 00:41:45.385
It's going to make you die early. I told you to quit.

588
00:41:46.056 --> 00:41:48.295
I didn't know you'd be here.

589
00:41:48.295 --> 00:41:49.425
My gosh. seriously.

590
00:41:51.166 --> 00:41:53.536
Is there something wrong? Are you sick?

591
00:41:58.235 --> 00:42:00.405
I just missed you.

592
00:42:00.976 --> 00:42:03.575
I missed you so much that I thought I might die.

593
00:42:03.806 --> 00:42:05.376
Don't ever say you might die.

594
00:42:08.445 --> 00:42:09.545
Ji Na.

595
00:42:09.545 --> 00:42:11.945
You told me you'll do anything I want. right?

596
00:42:11.945 --> 00:42:13.655
Yes. What do you want? Just say it.

597
00:42:14.755 --> 00:42:16.286
Just treat me like usual.

598
00:42:17.056 --> 00:42:18.056
What?

599
00:42:18.056 --> 00:42:20.155
Forget that I'm sick.

600
00:42:20.155 --> 00:42:22.865
Just treat me like you usually do. Talk to me about random things.

601
00:42:22.865 --> 00:42:25.595
eat with me. and nag at me.

602
00:42:25.595 --> 00:42:26.965
That's how I want you to treat me.

603
00:42:28.865 --> 00:42:32.036
That's what I want from you.

604
00:42:36.146 --> 00:42:38.146
I'm hungry. Should we order jokbal?

605
00:42:38.976 --> 00:42:40.275
Jokbal sounds great.

606
00:42:41.345 --> 00:42:42.416
A medium-sized serving or large?

607
00:42:42.746 --> 00:42:45.416
A large. Obviously.

608
00:42:45.416 --> 00:42:47.155
- And order buckwheat noodles. - Got it.

609
00:42:48.516 --> 00:42:51.025
- It's going to taste amazing. - I was going to go on a diet.

610
00:42:55.525 --> 00:42:56.525
My gosh.

611
00:42:56.525 --> 00:42:59.965
We haven't shopped for groceries together in ages.

612
00:43:02.635 --> 00:43:04.005
Buy your beer with your own money.

613
00:43:07.336 --> 00:43:08.706
By the way. who was that girl?

614
00:43:11.876 --> 00:43:15.345
You know. that girl from work.

615
00:43:16.345 --> 00:43:17.646
You guys looked pretty close.

616
00:43:29.766 --> 00:43:30.825
Hello.

617
00:43:30.825 --> 00:43:32.396
- Hello. - Hello.

618
00:43:39.306 --> 00:43:40.336
What's wrong?

619
00:43:42.646 --> 00:43:44.845
- There was a car behind you. - A car?

620
00:43:45.615 --> 00:43:47.345
What car? There's no car.

621
00:43:47.976 --> 00:43:50.045
There was one just now. It was actually a baby stroller.

622
00:43:52.286 --> 00:43:54.286
Did I almost get hit by a baby stroller?

623
00:43:54.985 --> 00:43:57.586
We both almost got hit by it.

624
00:43:58.456 --> 00:44:00.595
I wanted to see her face.

625
00:44:00.825 --> 00:44:03.425
But I couldn't because I had to greet customers.

626
00:44:08.295 --> 00:44:09.365
Aren't you going to introduce me?

627
00:44:09.365 --> 00:44:11.505
- It's not like that. - Then what is it?

628
00:44:11.865 --> 00:44:13.476
- Just... - Just what?

629
00:44:14.175 --> 00:44:15.706
Just a writer.

630
00:44:15.706 --> 00:44:17.905
Stop lying to me. will you?

631
00:44:17.905 --> 00:44:19.715
I saw the look on your face.

632
00:44:20.715 --> 00:44:22.715
You always do that.

633
00:44:22.715 --> 00:44:24.746
You act first. then find out later.

634
00:44:25.146 --> 00:44:27.155
Your brain is slower than your body.

635
00:44:27.586 --> 00:44:29.356
It's not good to be too smart.

636
00:44:31.956 --> 00:44:33.356
Hello? What...

637
00:44:35.126 --> 00:44:36.166
Hello?

638
00:44:36.865 --> 00:44:37.896
Hey.

639
00:44:39.166 --> 00:44:42.095
Where are you? Okay.

640
00:44:44.106 --> 00:44:45.365
I have to go.

641
00:44:45.606 --> 00:44:47.675
- Where? - The kid just called.

642
00:44:47.675 --> 00:44:49.845
and he's out of it. He's bawling and losing it.

643
00:44:49.845 --> 00:44:51.575
- What kid? - Sun Kyung.

644
00:44:51.575 --> 00:44:53.275
Later. See you at home.

645
00:44:53.916 --> 00:44:55.016
Hey.

646
00:44:56.416 --> 00:44:59.316
Whenever I vented

647
00:44:59.715 --> 00:45:02.825
Because I was lonely

648
00:45:03.786 --> 00:45:08.795
You came to me with love

649
00:45:10.295 --> 00:45:13.365
And with your pretty smile

650
00:45:13.735 --> 00:45:16.965
With your pretty love

651
00:45:17.465 --> 00:45:24.175
You embraced my heart

652
00:45:24.175 --> 00:45:28.115
My sister

653
00:45:29.686 --> 00:45:32.045
Hey. Why aren't you answering your phone?

654
00:45:32.345 --> 00:45:34.586
What are you doing here?

655
00:45:35.115 --> 00:45:36.485
You called me.

656
00:45:36.755 --> 00:45:37.755
I did?

657
00:45:38.325 --> 00:45:40.095
I called you?

658
00:45:41.856 --> 00:45:44.666
You're right. I did.

659
00:45:45.496 --> 00:45:46.965
This kid's wasted.

660
00:45:47.566 --> 00:45:49.806
What's wrong? What is it?

661
00:45:51.306 --> 00:45:53.135
- Sir. - Yes?

662
00:45:53.306 --> 00:45:55.575
Sir!

663
00:45:56.806 --> 00:46:00.045
Gosh. What is it? What?

664
00:46:01.345 --> 00:46:02.945
Were you dumped?

665
00:46:03.885 --> 00:46:06.215
Don't do anything you'll regret.

666
00:46:07.516 --> 00:46:10.226
You know. the thing is...

667
00:46:10.226 --> 00:46:12.925
"Later" is all useless.

668
00:46:13.295 --> 00:46:16.025
You have to do it now. You'll regret it if you don't.

669
00:46:16.166 --> 00:46:18.195
So don't push things off to later.

670
00:46:18.195 --> 00:46:20.166
Do it all now. Now.

671
00:46:21.066 --> 00:46:22.336
Got that?

672
00:46:23.465 --> 00:46:26.775
You'll regret it. You'll regret it all your life.

673
00:46:26.876 --> 00:46:28.575
You'll keep regretting it.

674
00:46:28.936 --> 00:46:30.575
You'll really. really regret it.

675
00:46:33.275 --> 00:46:34.775
Why are you talking down to me?

676
00:46:37.246 --> 00:46:38.445
I'm so drunk.

677
00:47:00.606 --> 00:47:01.876
Ji Na. your phone.

678
00:47:04.146 --> 00:47:05.445
Your phone's ringing.

679
00:47:16.885 --> 00:47:17.925
This is nice.

680
00:47:18.786 --> 00:47:19.856
Should I take it?

681
00:47:24.066 --> 00:47:25.126
Who could that be?

682
00:47:34.075 --> 00:47:35.275
Mr. Cha.

683
00:47:38.905 --> 00:47:40.146
Your hair looks nice.

684
00:47:40.976 --> 00:47:42.316
So...

685
00:47:44.246 --> 00:47:45.345
the two of you...

686
00:47:46.016 --> 00:47:48.885
entered into a contract separately on your own.

687
00:47:50.985 --> 00:47:52.155
What happened was...

688
00:47:52.155 --> 00:47:53.425
It was a waste.

689
00:47:53.425 --> 00:47:56.566
It was obvious she'd do well with some guidance.

690
00:47:57.766 --> 00:48:00.436
- You were being thoughtful. - It was sympathy.

691
00:48:00.896 --> 00:48:02.195
Are you just working together?

692
00:48:02.195 --> 00:48:04.465
Of course. Don't be silly.

693
00:48:04.465 --> 00:48:06.876
You must do things other than work with your writers.

694
00:48:06.876 --> 00:48:09.005
Yes. I eat with them. have coffee with them.

695
00:48:09.005 --> 00:48:10.646
and take walks with them at times.

696
00:48:10.646 --> 00:48:13.275
I'm not saying the two of you should do that.

697
00:48:13.275 --> 00:48:15.715
I'll keep that in mind if I want to do something else.

698
00:48:15.715 --> 00:48:18.545
See that? This jerk never lets you have the last word.

699
00:48:18.545 --> 00:48:19.615
- Right. - "This jerk"?

700
00:48:19.615 --> 00:48:21.956
I quit. remember? When else can I give you an attitude?

701
00:48:22.255 --> 00:48:24.726
Anyway. I'm done questioning you.

702
00:48:24.726 --> 00:48:26.195
I'll bow out now.

703
00:48:27.126 --> 00:48:29.295
- You're leaving? Already? - Yes.

704
00:48:29.626 --> 00:48:32.695
I have someone waiting for me at home as well.

705
00:48:32.695 --> 00:48:33.795
Later.

706
00:48:34.735 --> 00:48:36.206
I put you down as on leave.

707
00:48:36.766 --> 00:48:40.036
Tell them to fire me. I want to collect unemployment.

708
00:48:40.036 --> 00:48:42.536
Tell Mr. Park yourself. Stop screening his calls.

709
00:48:43.445 --> 00:48:45.146
When else can I screen his calls?

710
00:48:45.146 --> 00:48:46.215
I'm out for real.

711
00:48:47.316 --> 00:48:48.316
Bye.

712
00:48:49.016 --> 00:48:50.016
Bye.

713
00:48:55.885 --> 00:48:58.655
She seems pretty well for now.

714
00:48:58.786 --> 00:49:01.525
I don't know if she's well or pretending to be.

715
00:49:04.195 --> 00:49:05.865
What brings you here. Mr. Cha?

716
00:49:06.365 --> 00:49:08.496
Am I "Mr. Cha" to you too?

717
00:49:08.496 --> 00:49:11.336
- You were worried about me. right? - I was worried about the series.

718
00:49:13.536 --> 00:49:15.876
Sorry for making you see that the other day.

719
00:49:16.206 --> 00:49:17.306
Sorry.

720
00:49:17.746 --> 00:49:20.075
I said I was worried about the series.

721
00:49:21.476 --> 00:49:22.545
Did you write a lot?

722
00:49:24.316 --> 00:49:26.956
You always catch me at my worst.

723
00:49:28.816 --> 00:49:30.086
Why does that always happen?

724
00:49:30.086 --> 00:49:31.456
It's because I'm kind.

725
00:49:32.556 --> 00:49:34.356
- What? - Because of my great character.

726
00:49:34.356 --> 00:49:36.226
I can't ignore a woman who's crying.

727
00:49:36.295 --> 00:49:38.695
You could sense a kind person.

728
00:49:38.825 --> 00:49:42.365
You could sense that. and I happened to be there.

729
00:49:42.465 --> 00:49:43.536
Every time.

730
00:49:44.306 --> 00:49:45.606
You're so funny.

731
00:49:45.735 --> 00:49:47.106
I hear that often.

732
00:49:47.775 --> 00:49:49.445
I didn't mean you're actually funny.

733
00:49:49.606 --> 00:49:51.005
Can't you pick up on sarcasm?

734
00:49:51.376 --> 00:49:53.775
Well... I heard that often as well.

735
00:49:58.485 --> 00:50:00.985
I didn't come to talk about nonsense like this.

736
00:50:02.885 --> 00:50:04.385
I came to tell you something.

737
00:50:04.686 --> 00:50:07.356
I didn't think I should hold off any longer. or...

738
00:50:07.356 --> 00:50:08.356
What is it?

739
00:50:11.425 --> 00:50:13.865
I don't know where to start.

740
00:50:15.795 --> 00:50:17.836
I didn't intend it from the start.

741
00:50:21.005 --> 00:50:22.005
Just a minute.

742
00:50:22.806 --> 00:50:24.476
Dong Kyung must've forgotten something.

743
00:51:07.155 --> 00:51:08.655
Sorry for not showing up.

744
00:51:09.186 --> 00:51:10.286
You startled me.

745
00:51:13.155 --> 00:51:15.595
But you really are a troublemaker.

746
00:51:15.825 --> 00:51:17.595
How could you say you'll jump?

747
00:51:20.295 --> 00:51:23.836
Wait. So you heard me but you didn't come?

748
00:51:27.005 --> 00:51:28.606
Face forward. The light changed.

749
00:51:52.836 --> 00:51:54.195
What is this?

750
00:51:56.735 --> 00:51:59.066
You said you were happy that day.

751
00:52:21.496 --> 00:52:25.525
Seriously. You are very useful.

752
00:52:33.235 --> 00:52:34.876
Why do you keep staring?

753
00:52:34.876 --> 00:52:35.905
Because you're in front of me.

754
00:52:35.905 --> 00:52:38.775
Then what? Should I go next to you?

755
00:52:39.976 --> 00:52:41.816
I can't. It'll mess up the balance.

756
00:52:49.316 --> 00:52:50.686
How pretty.

757
00:52:51.686 --> 00:52:53.755
Like it'll disappear.

758
00:52:55.825 --> 00:52:58.266
Everything that disappears is usually beautiful.

759
00:53:08.976 --> 00:53:10.746
When I disappeared.

760
00:53:12.146 --> 00:53:14.445
you said no one remembered me.

761
00:53:15.516 --> 00:53:16.586
Yes.

762
00:53:20.255 --> 00:53:21.916
I hope that happens...

763
00:53:23.626 --> 00:53:25.325
when I die.

764
00:53:27.556 --> 00:53:29.325
I want the people I leave behind...

765
00:53:30.396 --> 00:53:32.396
to forget all about me.

766
00:53:33.365 --> 00:53:35.735
So they wouldn't be sad because of me.

767
00:53:37.965 --> 00:53:40.075
I hope I will...

768
00:53:40.675 --> 00:53:44.606
disappear like that. As if I'm evaporating.

769
00:53:53.985 --> 00:53:55.385
By any chance...

770
00:53:58.056 --> 00:53:59.126
can I...

771
00:54:01.195 --> 00:54:03.425
make a wish for that...

772
00:54:41.135 --> 00:54:43.005
You always surprise me like that.

773
00:54:43.905 --> 00:54:44.936
What do you mean?

774
00:54:46.336 --> 00:54:48.476
- You know... - Is it about the kiss?

775
00:54:48.476 --> 00:54:52.945
My gosh. You didn't have to specify it like that.

776
00:54:53.976 --> 00:54:55.976
Don't use your wish for other people.

777
00:55:05.255 --> 00:55:08.396
I can do some things for you like today.

778
00:55:09.255 --> 00:55:11.766
So I want you to think harder about it and use it for yourself.

779
00:55:12.166 --> 00:55:13.266
So you have no regrets.

780
00:55:17.436 --> 00:55:20.005
I already tried to use the wish for myself.

781
00:55:22.735 --> 00:55:24.606
But you didn't grant me that wish.

782
00:55:26.376 --> 00:55:27.416
I want you...

783
00:55:29.246 --> 00:55:31.045
to love me.

784
00:55:33.885 --> 00:55:37.286
Can I wish for that too?

785
00:55:39.126 --> 00:55:40.155
No.

786
00:55:40.795 --> 00:55:43.595
You said no to my wish.

787
00:55:51.135 --> 00:55:53.036
You don't have to wish for that.

788
00:55:56.775 --> 00:55:58.075
What did you mean by that?

789
00:55:59.505 --> 00:56:00.545
Sorry...

790
00:56:01.275 --> 00:56:02.476
Are you okay?

791
00:56:03.516 --> 00:56:04.586
Are you okay?

792
00:56:08.516 --> 00:56:09.615
Are you okay?

793
00:56:19.496 --> 00:56:21.536
I'm sorry. Sorry about that.

794
00:56:23.106 --> 00:56:25.706
- Dong Kyung. Sun Kyung. - Mom!

795
00:56:27.635 --> 00:56:29.905
All right. Let's have some cotton candy...

796
00:56:29.905 --> 00:56:32.146
and get on the Ferris wheel.

797
00:56:36.246 --> 00:56:38.786
(1.894 days with you at Kyungjun World)

798
00:56:39.345 --> 00:56:40.615
I thought you'd want to see them.

799
00:56:55.795 --> 00:56:57.606
You could see them only for a brief moment.

800
00:57:02.905 --> 00:57:05.476
Did I mess up again?

801
00:57:11.916 --> 00:57:12.916
No.

802
00:57:14.516 --> 00:57:16.056
I'm happy.

803
00:57:18.325 --> 00:57:19.525
I am happy.

804
00:57:21.325 --> 00:57:22.795
I was happy just now.

805
00:57:24.226 --> 00:57:25.525
I was utterly happy.

806
00:57:33.306 --> 00:57:34.306
Tak Dong Kyung.

807
00:57:35.536 --> 00:57:37.945
- Yes? - Like me.

808
00:57:43.115 --> 00:57:44.316
It's okay to like me.

809
00:57:46.215 --> 00:57:48.786
I don't care about anyone but you now.

810
00:57:51.226 --> 00:57:52.726
You don't have to wish for it.

811
00:57:53.126 --> 00:57:54.425
That's my answer.

812
00:57:54.695 --> 00:57:56.356
